});

// listen for incoming messages
bot.on('message', (ctx) => {
  // echo the message back to the user
  ctx.reply(`You said: ${ctx.message.text}`);
});

// start the bot
bot.start();
```

This example sets up a bot that responds to the `/start` and `/help` commands, as well as any other messages sent to it. When a user sends a `/start` command, it sends a welcome message, and when a user sends a `/help` command, it sends a help message. The `bot.on('message')` listener echoes the user's message back to them.

