Here's an example code snippet using Telegraf library in Node.js to reply to a message in the same group and on the same topic:

```
const Telegraf = require('telegraf');

const bot = new Telegraf(process.env.BOT_TOKEN);

bot.on('text', (ctx) => {
  // Reply to message in the same chat
  ctx.reply('Hello, world!', { reply_to_message_id: ctx.message.message_id });
});

bot.launch();
```

In this example, the `reply_to_message_id` option is used to specify the ID of the original message in the current chat that the bot is replying to. This ensures that the reply is posted to the same group and on the same topic as the original message.

