To determine whether a text message received by a Telegram bot is part of a group chat or a personal chat, you can use the `ctx.chat.type` property provided by the `telegraf` library in Node.js. If the value of `ctx.chat.type` is `'private'`, it is a personal chat, and if the value is `'group'` or `'supergroup'`, it is a group chat. 

Here is an example code snippet:

```
bot.on('text', async (ctx) => {
  if (ctx.chat.type === 'private') {
    // Handle personal chat message
  } else {
    // Handle group chat message
  }
})
```

Note that this only applies to text messages. Other types of messages, such as photos or videos, may have a different `ctx.chat.type` value.
